comments.body:
@rhatdan I am creating the image volumes within the container directory, basically if the dockerfile has a VOLUME /myvol and we want to bind mount it, the volume is created in /var/lib/containers/storage/container-id/volumes/myvol. So when the container is removed, the volume is automatically removed.
We had a discussion that there is no point putting it outside the container state directory as we don't support sharing of volumes.
I am a bit confused, where would these volumes that we want to remove with podman rm --volumes live?
